      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="875-29AI" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">The following POEM being upon a Certain D<hi rend="underline">ean</hi> who has purchased a Piece of Ground from a certain Gentleman in the Country, call'd, Sir <hi rend="underline">Arthur</hi>, and is building a fine House upon it, which he calls <hi rend="underline">Drapier's-Hall</hi>, at the the Request of the said Sir <hi rend="underline">Arthur</hi>, we are perswaded it will not be unacceptable to the Publick.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">W</hi>e give the World to understand,</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-line-2"> Our thriving <hi rend="underline">Dean</hi> has purchased Land,</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-line-3"> A Purchase which will bring him clear,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-line-4"> Above his Rent────<hi rend="underline">Four Pound</hi> a Year?</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-line-5"> Provided to improve the Ground,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-line-6"> He will but add <hi rend="underline">two hundred Pound</hi>;</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-line-7"> And from his endless hoarded Store,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-line-8"> To build a House────<hi rend="underline">Five hundred</hi> more.</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-line-9"> Sir <hi rend="underline">Arthur</hi> too, shall have his Will,</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-line-10"> And call the Mansion <hi rend="underline">DRAPIERS HILL</hi>,</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-line-11"> That when a Nation long en────d,</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-line-12"> Forgets by whom it once was saved;</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-line-13"> When none the <hi rend="underline">Draper's</hi> Praise shall sing,</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-line-14"> His <hi rend="underline">Signs</hi> aloft no longer swing,<gap/><gap/></l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-line-15"> His <hi rend="underline">Medals</hi> and his <hi rend="underline">Prints</hi> forgotten,</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-line-16"> And all his <hi rend="underline">Handkerchiefs</hi> are rotten,</l><l n="17" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-line-17"> His <hi rend="underline">famous Letters</hi> made waste Paper,</l><l n="18" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-line-18"> This Hill may keep the Name of <hi rend="underline">DRAPIER</hi>,</l><l n="19" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-line-19"> In spight of Envy flourish still,</l><l n="20" xml:id="spp-875-29AI-line-20"> And <hi rend="underline">Drapier's</hi> vye with <hi rend="underline">Cooper's Hill</hi>.875-29AI   </l></lg></div>
